---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const LAST_UPDATED = '2026-06-24';
---

<Base title="now" description="What I'm doing right now.">
  <div class="section-label"># now</div>
  <h1>what i'm up to</h1>

  <p class="now-meta">
    last updated: {LAST_UPDATED} ·
    <a href="https://nownownow.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">what is this?</a>
  </p>

  <div class="now-block">
    <div class="now-block-label">working on</div>
    <ul class="now-list">
      <span class="now-item-name">Seraph</span>
      <li>
        <span class="now-item-name">seraph</span>
        — I am working on getting Seraph to support more complex ARM neon assembly kernels and optimizations, testing those optimizations and benchmarking them.
        Currently the kernel library supports 5 kernels, I will now be going into more LLM related algorithms, so that it is in parallel with Axiom. I am also actively writing blogs
        for Seraph. 
      <li>
        <span class="now-item-name">tesserae</span>
        — I am trying to get Tesserae work with more complex optimizations such as warp specs and higher swizzles.  
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="now-item-name">axiom</span>
        — working on getting coherent outputs from Llama 3.2 1B then go on to more complex models. I am also building an Apple Metal compatibility to maybe 
        locally host the model in the future. So along with Seraph, I am also learning a lot of the Apple Metal Rust bindings called objc2_metal.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="now-block">
    <div class="now-block-label">reading</div>
    <ul class="now-list">
      <li>
        <span class="now-item-name">ARM NEON</span>
        - I have been reading about the ARM C intrinsic library, ARM A profile architecture guide and also Apple Metal bindings for Axiom. It is more SIMD focused considering
        Seraph is essentially a SIMD kernel library.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="now-item-name">OCaml and OxCaml</span>
        - I am trying to learn OCaml as I want to write more functional programming code and also use it for some of my projects. As a consequence I am also learning OxCaml. 
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="now-item-name">Emacs Guide and Linux Ricing</span>
        - I building my own custom Emacs setup as I have now a CachyOS system! Will also be ricing it so I am surfing various repos. 
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="now-block">
    <div class="now-block-label">based in</div>
    <ul class="now-list">
      <li>Bangalore, India</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Base>
